{"pageProps":{"eyebrow":"工具链","page":{"layout":"document","title":"usage","description":"This is an adapted version of opensnoop from bcc/libbpf-tools, you can check our source code here: examples/bpftools/opensnoop","bodyHtml":"<h2 id=\"example\">example</h2>\n<p>This is an adapted version of opensnoop from <a href=\"https://github.com/iovisor/bcc/blob/master/libbpf-tools/opensnoop.bpf.c\">bcc/libbpf-tools</a>, you can check our source code here: <a href=\"https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/eunomia-bpf/tree/master/examples/bpftools/opensnoop\">examples/bpftools/opensnoop</a></p>\n<p>Compile the <a href=\"https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/eunomia-bpf/tree/master/examples/bpftools/opensnoop\">opensnoop</a> example locally like this:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">$</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> cd</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> examples/bpftools/opensnoop</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">$</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> docker</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> run</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> -it</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> -v</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> /userpath/eunomia-bpf/examples/bpftools/opensnoop:/src</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> ghcr.io/eunomia-bpf/ecc-`</span><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">uname</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> -m</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">`</span><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">:latest</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<p><code>userpath</code> needs to be replaced with your own repo path.</p>\n<p>After compile the eBPF code, you can define a config file like this:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"yaml\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"yaml\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#8DDB8C\">programs</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">:</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">  - </span><span style=\"color:#8DDB8C\">name</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">: </span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">opensnoop</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#8DDB8C\">    metrics</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">:</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#8DDB8C\">      counters</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">:</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">        - </span><span style=\"color:#8DDB8C\">name</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">: </span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">eunomia_file_open_counter</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#8DDB8C\">          description</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">: </span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">test</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#8DDB8C\">          labels</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">:</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">            - </span><span style=\"color:#8DDB8C\">name</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">: </span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">pid</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">            - </span><span style=\"color:#8DDB8C\">name</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">: </span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">comm</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">            - </span><span style=\"color:#8DDB8C\">name</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">: </span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">filename</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#8DDB8C\">              from</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">: </span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">fname</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#8DDB8C\">    compiled_ebpf_filename</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">: </span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">package.json</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<p>use the path to <code>package.json</code> as compiled_ebpf_filename in the config file. You can find the example at <a href=\"https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/eunomia-bpf/blob/master/examples/bpftools/opensnoop/config.yaml\">config.yaml</a>.</p>\n<p>Then, you can start the exporter:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"shellsession\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"shellsession\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">$ ls</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">config.yaml  eunomia-exporter package.json</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">$ sudo ./eunomia-exporter</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">Running ebpf program opensnoop takes 46 ms</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">Listening on http://127.0.0.1:8526</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">running and waiting for the ebpf events from perf event...</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">Receiving request at path /metrics</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<p>Different from the bcc ebpf_exporter, the only thing you need to run on the deployment machine is the <code>config file</code> and <code>package.json</code>. There is no need to install <code>LLVM/CLang</code> for BCC.</p>\n<p>The result is:</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://oss.openanolis.cn/sig/stxfomyiiwdwkdrqwlnn\" alt=\"prometheus\"></p>\n<h2 id=\"manage-ebpf-tracing-program-via-api\">manage eBPF tracing program via API</h2>\n<p>start an eBPF exporter via web API:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"shellsession\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"shellsession\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">$ curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8526/start -H </span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">\"Content-Type: application/json\"</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> -d @examples/opensnoop/curl_post_example.json</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">{\"id\":1}</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<p>see <a href=\"https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/eunomia-bpf/blob/master/eunomia-exporter/examples/opensnoop/curl_post_example.json\">curl_post_example.json</a> for the example of the request body.</p>\n<p>list all running eBPF programs:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"shellsession\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"shellsession\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">$ curl http://127.0.0.1:8526/list</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">[{\"id\":0,\"name\":\"bootstrap\"},{\"id\":1,\"name\":\"opensnoop\"}]</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<p>stop an eBPF program:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">$</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> curl</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> -X</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> POST</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> http://127.0.0.1:8526/stop</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> -H</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> \"Content-Type: application/json\"</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> -d</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> '{\"id\": 1}'</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<p>documents:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"shellsession\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"shellsession\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">$ cargo build --release</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">$ target/release/eunomia-exporter -h</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">eunomia-exporter 0.1.0</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">USAGE:</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">    eunomia-exporter [OPTIONS]</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">OPTIONS:</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">    -c, --config &#x3C;CONFIG>    Sets a custom config file [default: config.yaml]</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">    -h, --help               Print help information</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">    -V, --version            Print version information</span></span></code></pre></figure>","headings":[{"id":"example","text":"example","depth":2},{"id":"manage-ebpf-tracing-program-via-api","text":"manage eBPF tracing program via API","depth":2}],"sourcePath":"https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/eunomia.dev/tree/main/docs/eunomia-bpf/exporter/usage.md","metadata":{"updatedAt":"2026-03-08T04:58:07.000Z","createdAt":"2023-08-10T12:54:12.000Z","authors":[{"name":"云微","email":"1067852565@qq.com"},{"name":"oluceps","email":"ospp@oluceps.uk"}]},"path":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/exporter/usage/","alternates":{"en":"/eunomia-bpf/exporter/usage/","zh":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/exporter/usage/"},"continuation":{"index":{"title":"eunomia-bpf：简化并增强eBPF，支持CO-RE[^1]和WebAssembly[^2]","description":"![GitHub release (latest by date)](https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/eunomia-bpf/releases) ![codecov](https://codecov.io/gh/eunomia-bpf/eunomia-bpf) ![DeepSource](https://deepsource.io/gh/eunomia-bpf/eunomia-bpf/?ref=reposi","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/"},"previous":{"title":"exporter","description":"An prometheus and OpenTelemetry exporter for custom eBPF metrics, written in async rust: eunomia-exporter","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/exporter/"},"next":{"title":"introduction","description":"eunomia-bpf is a dynamic loading library/runtime and a compile toolchain framework, aim at helping you build and distribute eBPF programs easier.","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/introduction/"}},"sidebar":[{"title":"eunomia-bpf：简化并增强eBPF，支持CO-RE[^1]和WebAssembly[^2]","items":[{"title":"eunomia-bpf：简化并增强eBPF，支持CO-RE[^1]和WebAssembly[^2]","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/","depth":0},{"title":"Project architecture","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/architecture/","depth":1},{"title":"benchmark","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/benchmark/","depth":1},{"title":"ecc docker usage","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/ecc/docker-usage/","depth":2},{"title":"github template","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/ecc/github-template/","depth":2},{"title":"eunomia-cc","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/ecc/","depth":1},{"title":"ecc usage","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/ecc/usage/","depth":2},{"title":"ecli dockerfile usage","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/ecli/ecli-dockerfile-usage/","depth":2},{"title":"ecli","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/ecli/","depth":1},{"title":"ecli server","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/ecli/server/","depth":2},{"title":"exporter","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/exporter/","depth":1},{"title":"usage","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/exporter/usage/","depth":2},{"title":"introduction","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/introduction/","depth":1},{"title":"eunomia-bpf 用户手册: 让 eBPF 程序的开发和部署尽可能简单","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/manual/","depth":1},{"title":"在线体验网站","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/online/","depth":1},{"title":"quickstart","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/quickstart/","depth":1},{"title":"build on android aarch64","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/setup/build-android-arm/","depth":2},{"title":"build from source","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/setup/build/","depth":2},{"title":"Install ecli and ecc","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/setup/","depth":1},{"title":"supporting-external-BTF","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/supporting-external-BTF/","depth":1},{"title":"video","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/video/","depth":1}]}]}},"__N_SSG":true}